# Lychee Link Checker Ignore File
# https://lychee.cli.rs/
#
# TODO (template users): After customizing the project, remove placeholder
#   URL patterns and add patterns for any external URLs specific to your
#   project that are intermittently unavailable in CI.

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Template placeholder URLs (not real links)
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# These appear in template files and get replaced during
# project customization.

# GitHub placeholder URLs for template users
https://github\.com/\[OWNER\]/\[REPO\]
https://github\.com/YOURNAME/YOURREPO
https://YOURNAME\.github\.io/YOURREPO

# Example URLs in documentation templates
https://github\.com/example.*

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Template placeholder file paths
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# These are example paths in template.md that aren't real files.

file://.*path/to/file
file://.*path/to/other-file
file://.*docs/adr/NNN-related\.md
file://.*docs/adr/XXX-name\.md

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Local / development URLs
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# These are valid in development but never reachable from CI.

https?://localhost[:/].*
https?://127\.0\.0\.1[:/].*
https?://0\.0\.0\.0[:/].*
https?://\[::1\][:/].*

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Inherited template paths that don't exist in this project
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# The fork-bring-up retains many template-grade docs as reference
# (see fork policy in `.github/copilot-instructions.md`). These
# references survive in inherited content scheduled for rewrite;
# matching them here keeps the link-checker hard-failing on real
# regressions without forcing a doc-wide rewrite mid-Phase.
file://.*/simple_python_boilerplate(/.*)?$
file://.*/simple-python-boilerplate\.code-workspace
file://.*/git-config-reference\.md.*
file://.*/requirements(-dev)?\.txt
file://.*/db(/.*)?$
file://.*/var/?$
file://.*/docs/notes/learning(-web-apps)?\.md.*
file://.*/docs/guide/getting-started\.md
file://.*/tests/unit/test_example\.py
file://.*/tests/integration/sql/?$
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# External hosts intermittently unreachable from GitHub-hosted runners
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# OpenSSF Scorecard's marketing site refuses connections from a subset
# of GitHub Actions egress IPs. The repo's actual scorecard report is
# fetched via the GitHub Action, not this URL.
https://scorecard\.dev/?$

# cursor.sh marketing site intermittently times out from CI runners.
https://cursor\.sh


file://.*/docs/reference/template-inventory\.md
# ADRs that reference removed template tooling and are slated for
# rewrite per the fork policy (see spec § "ADRs to Write").
file://.*/docs/adr/011-repository-guard-pattern\.md
file://.*/docs/adr/036-diagnostic-tooling-strategy\.md
file://.*/docs/adr/040-v1-release-readiness\.md
file://.*/docs/adr/041-env-inspect-web-dashboard\.md
file://.*/docs/adr/042-script-smoke-testing\.md
file://.*/docs/adr/043-collector-plugin-architecture\.md

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# External URLs with intermittent availability
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# These are valid URLs but sometimes fail in CI due to
# certificate issues, rate limiting, or temporary outages.

# Conventional commits - sometimes has certificate issues in CI
https://www\.conventionalcommits\.org

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Release-please compare URLs
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Release-please generates compare URLs (e.g. v0.4.0...v0.5.0) in
# CHANGELOG.md before the tag exists.  The URL 404s until the
# release PR is merged and the tag is created.
https://github\.com/.*/compare/v.*\.\.\.v.*

# The Hitchhiker's Guide to Python - intermittent certificate errors
https://docs\.python-guide\.org

# Taskfile.dev - occasionally has certificate issues
https://taskfile\.dev

# Scientific Python - occasionally unavailable
https://learn\.scientific-python\.org

# GitHub CLI - manual/installation path sometimes 404s
https://cli\.github\.com/manual/installation

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Sites that block automated crawlers / rate-limit aggressively
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# CSS-Tricks rejects non-browser requests (415 Unsupported Media Type)
https://css-tricks\.com

# LinkedIn blocks all non-browser requests
https://www\.linkedin\.com

# Twitter / X.com aggressively rate-limits
https://(www\.)?(twitter\.com|x\.com)

# PyPI rate-limits CI runners
https://pypi\.org

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# GitHub URLs that require authentication or are generated
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# GitHub edit/settings pages require login and will always 404 in CI
https://github\.com/.*/settings
https://github\.com/.*/edit

# GitHub private profile URLs
https://github\.com/orgs/.*/teams
